Basic Installation
==================

NOTE: this will change in future versions: all files should belong to a 
special user, say 'lincs' and all users on the system should be part of 
group 'lincs'. User's 'lincs' account should be special: no shell, no login 
possible, etc. This is work in progress. 


3 easy steps:

    ./configure
    make

Switch to root and enter:

    make install

Eventually test it:

    make test


Components
----------

- binaries and configuration information is stored under /etc/lincs, unless
  you changed the installation prefix at configuration time. Those files
  have to reside on the root filesystem because it is the only one 
  guaranteed to be available. 

- header files are stored by default in /usr/local/include/cfgs

- log file is /tmp/lincs.log (FIXME)

